This paper proposes a new approach for reducing the complexity of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) while maintaining accuracy, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the impact of this approach on CNN training and inference, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a new type of convolutional kernel, which could be of interest to researchers in sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
